title: Behind the Scenes âˆ™ Fashionmilk "Sterrenmeisjes" Shoot â˜†
description:
Sweat was dripping down my back when Bianca Toeps (head of Fashionmilk.com) sent me the moodboard for Fashionmilk's 5th photoshoot. "I want Purple glitter hair!" she blurted out. "Hell NO!" I thought.

I had just mastered how to do fashionable waves at WE R Agency, I wasn't ready for Purple, nor glitter! Nonetheless, I couldn't say no to this amazing opportunity. An opportunity to finally put all my hard work at WE R to good use. An opportunity to for once in my life make Purple glitter hair! Hope you enjoy â™¡

title: Halloween: The Sad Clown Makeup Tutorial
description:
Artists like Pat McGrath & Alex Box have always inspired me like no other. Especially Alex Box has a way of making mesmerizing looks that you won't forget quickly. Alex recently did a very awesome grungy, goth look where her model had drips of Black and Grey running down her face. It was love at first sight. Immediately I started to think of ways how she made those perfect rained down drops.

Then I stumbled upon the legend Rick Baker's new Halloween tutorial. And there it was. In his video he showed exactly how Alex had done it. I decided to use his technique in my new Halloween tutorial and came up with something sad, devastating and a little dash of goth. I hope you enjoy my "Sad Clown". (Rick's tutorial: http://youtu.be/k0vpItYucNI )

title: Halloween: Plastic Fantastic Makeup Tutorial
description:
I've always been fascinated by plastic surgery. The way surgeons can completely change a face is pure magic to me. It wouldn't come as a surprise that shows like Dr. 90210 & The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills -or any of the bazillion housewives, as I think they all got something done- are one of my favorite shows to watch. 

A couple of weeks ago, as I was scrolling through my Instagram I stumbled upon a post by Instagram/Makeup God: @TheeVanityDiary. Ariel did a very awesome, very Nip/Tuck'ish look and I was blown away. From that moment on I knew I had to recreate this for one of my Halloween Tutorials this year. So, all credit for this look goes to him. I highly suggest looking him up, he has talent like no other. I'm sure you'll have fun scrolling the night away on his IG account -at least I did, haha- you can find Ariel's IG here: http://web.stagram.com/n/theevanitydiary/
